          "is_correct": false,
          "data_i18n": null
        },
        {
          "text": "p^k",
          "is_correct": false,
          "data_i18n": null
        }
      ],
      "explanation": "P(E) = 0 means the event is impossible; P(E) = 1 means it's certain. P(not E) = 1 - P(E) (complement rule). Probabilities always range from 0 to 1. The answer is C(n,k)p^k(1−p)^(n−k). The other options — 'n·p', 'C(n,k)', and 'p^k' — are related concepts but do not correctly answer this specific question."
